eThekwini Municipality said 82 of its buses had damaged windows caused by stone throwing. A statement released by the City on Saturday warned the public against throwing stones at the buses and the life threatening consequences of riding on the rear bumper of a moving bus. The municipality said Durban Transport has been faced with dangerous behavior conducted by young adults, including school children, in areas like uMlazi and Ntuzuma. The City said damaging municipal property was a criminal offence that may lead to possible prosecuting. "The City urges parents and the public to assist in stopping this dangerous behavior. The public can report any incident they witness to the police or the uMlazi depot on 031 906 2651 or Ntuzuma depot on 031 504 3421 or eThekwini Trasport Authority 082 268 4185," read the statement. 